 All must be removed. 

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:47.620
 Be careful when removing the back cover. 

00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:50.420
 since the two halves of the Game Boy are connected by a train. 

00:01:50.420 --> 00:01:53.540
 It must be disabled, but very carefully. 

00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:01.760
 After successfully disconnecting the loop, 

00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:05.420
 The back part can be postponed and completely go to the part with the screen. 

00:02:05.420 --> 00:02:07.840
 There are 10 more screws on the board, 

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:11.120
 but for them we already need the usual cross screwdriver. 

00:02:56.940 --> 00:02:59.520
 So we got to the screen. 

00:02:59.520 --> 00:03:03.280
 Now you need to remove a small rubber tape glued under it. 

00:03:03.280 --> 00:03:07.000
 This must be done very carefully so as not to damage the screen itself. 

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:09.440
 I personally used a small office knife, 

00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:11.160
 to gently pry her. 

00:03:15.580 --> 00:03:18.020
 The gum itself retired quite easily, 

00:03:18.020 --> 00:03:20.060
 but under it there was a very old layer of glue, 

00:03:20.060 --> 00:03:22.140
 which also had to be deleted. 

00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:34.480
 Now you need to connect both parts back 

00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:37.420
 and put something non-conductive between them. 

00:04:09.220 --> 00:04:11.240
 Well, now the fun part! 

00:04:11.240 --> 00:04:13.020
 To restore screen contact 

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:15.520
 It is necessary to warm the cable with a soldering iron. 

00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:17.300
 The main thing is not to overdo it. 

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:20.000
 and before starting, be sure to remove the soldering iron from the tip 

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:22.580
 all solder otherwise it will fall on the train. 

00:04:22.580 --> 00:04:26.480
 But after that we just drive a soldering iron under non-working columns. 

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:29.280
 and after seeing them gradually appear. 

